activities:
Zebra will use and otherwise process personal information about employees in the EU (including employees of its subsidiaries and affiliates) for the following purposes:

• Maintaining an internal telephone/e-mail directory;
• Managing business operations;
• Compensation decisions/bonus calculations;
• Performance management;
• Talent management/succession planning;
• Stock option and stock purchase plan administration; 
• Management of the recruitment process, including pre-employment checks; 
• Administering employee benefit plans, including health insurance plans; and
• Compliance with legal and regulatory requirements, and litigation-related rights and obligations;

Zebra will use and otherwise process personal information received about individual contacts of prospective and existing end users, distributors, other partners (“Customers”), suppliers, and other vendors (“Suppliers”) in the EU for the following purposes: 

• Purchase and delivery of Zebra products and services;
• Placing orders and checking status of orders; 
• Creating and maintaining user profile for future product ordering; 
• Responding to inquiries;
• Tailoring user’s experience;
• Assessing performance; 
• Protecting Zebra from fraud or inappropriate conduct;
• Operating the Zebra website and/or performing the associated business transactions;
• Protecting the security of the Zebra website;
• Providing access to the Zebra secure internet portal; and 
• Performing direct marketing activities and otherwise communicating information regarding Zebra products or services.
